com.samsung.android.sdk.mediacontrol

Interface SmcProvider.ResponseListener

  • Enclosing interface:
    SmcProvider

    public static interface SmcProvider.ResponseListener
    This listener interface provides the callback methods for response events.

      • onBrowse

        void onBrowse(SmcProvider smcProvider,
            List<SmcItem> smcItems,
            int requestedStartIndex,
            int requestedCount,
            SmcItem requestedFolder,
            boolean endOfItems,
            int error)
        Called when the response for SmcProvider.browse(SmcItem, int, int) is received.
        Parameters:
        smcProvider - The content provider instance.
        smcItems - The list of items returned. If no items are returned, this is an empty list.
        requestedStartIndex - The offset starting from zero that the browse method started from.
        requestedCount - The number of items requested .
        requestedFolder - The folder being browsed.
        endOfItems - Indicator that the browse method reached the end of the items in the folder. Set to true if the browse method reached the end of the items in the folder.
        error - The event status description. The valid values are:
        • Smc.SUCCESS
        • Smc.ERROR_BAD_RESPONSE
        • Smc.ERROR_UNKNOWN
        • Smc.ERROR_FEATURE_NOT_SUPPORTED
        • Smc.ERROR_INVALID_ARGUMENT
        • Smc.ERROR_INVALID_DEVICE
        • Smc.ERROR_INVALID_OBJECT
        • Smc.ERROR_ITEM_NOT_EXIST
        • Smc.ERROR_NETWORK_NOT_AVAILABLE
        • Smc.ERROR_NO_RESPONSE
        • Smc.ERROR_OUT_OF_MEMORY
        • Smc.ERROR_PERMISSION_NOT_ALLOWED
        • Smc.ERROR_SERVICE_NOT_CONNECTED
        • Smc.ERROR_TIME_OUT

      • onSearch

        void onSearch(SmcProvider smcProvider,
            List<SmcItem> smcItems,
            int requestedStartIndex,
            int requestedCount,
            SmcProvider.SearchCriteria searchCriteria,
            boolean endOfItems,
            int error)
        Called when the response for SmcProvider.search(SearchCriteria, int, int) is received
        Parameters:
        smcProvider - The content provider instance.
        smcItems - The search result. This is set to null if no items met the search criteria.
        requestedStartIndex - The offset starting from zero from which the search started.
        requestedCount - The number of items requested.
        searchCriteria - The criteria used to search for items.
        endOfItems - Indicator that the search method reached the end of the items in the folder. Set to true of the search method reached the end of the number of items in the folder.
        error - The event status description. The valid values are:
        • Smc.SUCCESS
        • Smc.ERROR_BAD_RESPONSE
        • Smc.ERROR_UNKNOWN
        • Smc.ERROR_FEATURE_NOT_SUPPORTED
        • Smc.ERROR_INVALID_ARGUMENT
        • Smc.ERROR_INVALID_DEVICE
        • Smc.ERROR_INVALID_OBJECT
        • Smc.ERROR_ITEM_NOT_EXIST
        • Smc.ERROR_NETWORK_NOT_AVAILABLE
        • Smc.ERROR_NO_RESPONSE
        • Smc.ERROR_OUT_OF_MEMORY
        • Smc.ERROR_PERMISSION_NOT_ALLOWED
        • Smc.ERROR_SERVICE_NOT_CONNECTED
        • Smc.ERROR_TIME_OUT
